    (2.2.) Suppliers


    1. TO DO

      - implement Supplier interface

    2. HOW

      - use a lambda expression or method reference to implement T get() method of the Supplier interface

    3. EQ.


    The implementation consists in providing a method that takes no arguments and returns the generic type.
    There is no requirement that a new or distinct result be returned each time the Supplier is returned. An eq. is Math.random which takes no argument and returns a double. This can be assgined to a Supplier reference and invoked at any time.
    One of the primary use cases for Suppliers is to support the concept of deferred execution - to ensure that a value is retrieved from a Supplier only when appropriate.
    See Also:
    LoggingWithASupplier, Recipe_6_1_Creating_An_Optional

      • useMathRandomAsASupplier

        protected static void useMathRandomAsASupplier()
        ◊◊◊ Use Math.random as a Supplier ◊◊◊ 
             // anonymous inner class implementation
     DoubleSupplier randomSupplier = new DoubleSupplier() {
        @Override
        public double getAsDouble() {
            return Math.random();
        }
     };

     // expression lambda
     randomSupplier = () -> Math.random();

     // method reference
     randomSupplier = Math::random;

     System.out.println(randomSupplier.getAsDouble());
